[1] Case update
- Mon 15 Jul 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=f09f479a42

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 14 Jul 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the number of accumulated cases is 2501, including 2407 confirmed and 94 probable. In total, there have been 1668 deaths (1574 in confirmed and 94 in probable cases) and 700 cases have recovered.
- 292 suspected cases under investigation;
-12 newly confirmed cases including 7 in Beni and 1 each in Oicha, Mutwanga, Kalunguta, Mandima, and Goma;
- The case of Goma will be reclassified as soon as the detailed investigations have accurately determined the health zone where [the case] developed symptoms.
- 6 new cases of confirmed deaths: 4 community deaths, including 3 in Beni and 1 in Oicha, and 2 deaths in CTEs, including 1 in Beni and 1 in Katwa;
Note: Of the 7 deaths reported 13 Jul 2019, 3 were non-cases and were removed from the database.
- 2 people treated at Butembo CTE [Ebola treatment centre] recovered.

