- Tue 16 Jul 2019. Helen Branswell
https://twitter.com/HelenBranswell

Further details on the pastor:

Helen Branswell
4. The priest's mother & sister live in South Kivu, a province which hasn't had Ebola cases; they were with him in the days leading up to his illness. They returned to their home, near the Rwandan border. The priest died from his infection. Potential here for bad developments.

3. It seems the discovery of an Ebola case in Goma may not have been as neat as was previously thought. The bus the priest traveled on broke down. He took a motorbike to Goma; the driver hasn't been found. The priest may have been symptomatic earlier than first believed.

